bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The World Student Christian Federation (WSCF) was founded in 1895 with the aim of uniting movements or associations of Christian students throughout the world. Since 1968 the WSCF has been decentralized into regions. There are currently six regions, each with its own regional office: Africa, Asia Pacific, Europe, Latin America and the Caribbean, Middle East, North America and Canada.

WSCF Europe is part of a global federation of grassroot Student Christian Movements (SCMs). These local organizations work on campuses and nationally to bring Christian students from all denominations together to work on issues of social justice. As a global organization the World Student Christian Federation connects SCMs through events, networks and solidarity/advocacy work. The WSCF Europe Region brings together students from 21 Student Christian Movements across Europe through international conferences, campaigns, and publications.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: These are the official archives of the World Student Christian Federation Europe Regional Office. The records have been organized as received, primarily according to a classification system provided by the WSCF Europe Region Office. They include administrative records, minutes, financial records, and documentation of conferences, workshops, and projects such as the Theological Project, Women's Project, Refugee Project, and East European Language and Leadership Training Project (Lingua Franca). An addendum to the collection integrated in 2017 contains similar documentation and has been retained primarily in the order in which it was received. There is considerable overlap between the various sub-series of the addendum.
